-- CNPC to Sell 20 Billion Yuan of 270-Day Bonds Jan. 5
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-01-04T05:51:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/cncp-plans-to-sell-20-billion-yuan-of-270-day-bonds-tomorrow.html
(Corrects the company name abbreviation in the headline.)  China National Petroleum Corp. (CNPZ) , the
nation’s biggest oil producer, plans to sell 20 billion yuan
($3.18 billion) of 270-day bonds on Jan. 5, the company said in
a statement.  The money will be used for working capital, the company
said in a prospectus filed with Chinabond, the nation’s bond
clearing house. Industrial & Commercial Bank of China Ltd. and
Bank of China Ltd. are the lead underwriters of the bond, the
document said.  The company produced 107.53 million metric tons of crude
oil in 2011, according to its online newsletter.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
